parameters:
Mage Relm: I'm not exactly sure... but the grimoire I have
is the original that sealed away the demons.

Mage Relm: I don't think that person can handle something
even advanced sorcerers find difficult to handle
accurately.

Thief Nora: Y-You should let go! I don't know what's going
on, but it looks like it's causing you pain!

Imperial Dark Agent Emoni: I-I can't let go... Without
this... I... I...!
Priestess Sophia: M-Monsters appearing out of nowhere...!?

Mage Relm: The grimoire of the demon of magic, Blarl...!
Caron, did you even possess a lost magic grimoire!?

Imperial Dark Agent Emoni: ...I-I don't want to die, I
don't want to be killed, I absolutely hate creating monsters
at the cost of lives!

Imperial Dark Agent Emoni: That's why, even if it means
sacrificing my own life, I don't want to die!
Thief Nora: You're too scared to even listen, huh!?
Clea: Then let's make her faint.
Priestess Sophia: Hehe, I thought so too.

Mage Relm: Let's see what happens when a spellcaster loses
their grimoire... Let's make her faint and take the grimoire
for sure!

Guild Leader Agonia: Is this one of the sources of monster
outbreaks?

Imperial Dark Agent Emoni: T-Thank goodness... I-I'm
alive... *panting* *panting* Ugh, Agonia-san... *sob*!

Guild Leader Agonia: I'm sure I told you before, you
shouldn't do things that are beyond your capabilities
without being prepared.

Imperial Dark Agent Emoni: Tha-thank you for saving me,
I-I'm so grateful...

Guild Leader Agonia: Although the grimoire has been
neutralized, will the monsters that have already appeared
disappear?

Mage Relm: Normally, that would be the case... but monsters
created from the grimoire might be an exception.

Mage Relm: The worst case scenario... is when the barely
controlled monsters go wild--

Thief Nora: This sound... It's coming from outside! There
are lots of footsteps heading towards the town!

Guild Leader Agonia: I will head to the main street. The
people living in that town are our precious comrades.
Clea: I'll go with you too.

Guild Leader Agonia: Clea and the others are heading
towards the dragon! We must quickly defeat it, or the entire
empire will be in danger.

Clea: When we fought the dragon, I felt something strange.
It felt different from the previous dragon, like it was
being [controlled].

Priestess Sophia: I also felt it, and... I don't think
Caron would resort to using something uncontrollable as a
trump card.

Priestess Sophia: There must be some way to control the
dragon.

Clea: They must be enjoying our suffering. The fact that
they made the dragon retreat back then is proof of that.

Guild Leader Agonia: Understood, from here on out, let's
act together.

Guild Leader Agonia: Take my hand, there must be something
we can do.

Guild Leader Agonia: Have you forgotten about the Great
Widow? We are here for the prayers of those without fangs.

Former guild member Emoni: Betraying that person... ugh...
but, still, sniff, I... I...

Guild Leader Agonia: As someone who shares the same master,
will you fight alongside me?

Former guild member Emoni: I will fight, I can fight! I
will atone for the sins I committed here, even if it's just
a little!

\CL Clea has \C[14]acquired the support skill Black Meteor
\C[0]and can now use it\|.

\CL Relm has \C[14]acquired the support skill Bon Apptit!
\C[0]and can now use it\|.
